;; Runtime Clojure namespace manifest for -PreleaseAot builds.
;;
;; Generated baseline (2026-07-17): full main-sourceSet namespace set, no
;; exclusions. An initial attempt to exclude datagen/** was reverted after
;; discovering cn.li.ac.core (a genuine runtime entry point) statically
;; requires cn.li.ac.datagen.bootstrap, which transitively requires the
;; ability/block/energy/wireless datagen registries and mcmod's
;; datagen.metadata -- datagen is not cleanly separable from the runtime
;; require graph in this codebase without a source-level bootstrap split
;; (out of scope here). This manifest currently exists for drift detection
;; only (verifyAotManifest) -- it does not yet reduce -PreleaseAot's compiled
;; namespace set below "everything". A future pass could shrink it by
;; computing genuine require-graph reachability from real entry points
;; instead of a directory-name heuristic.
;;
;; verifyAotManifest fails the build when source and this file drift apart in
;; either direction (namespace added to source but not here, or vice versa).

